{
  "uuid": "61cce73b9e4905b20e06116baaefe070",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Medical Technologist (ANATOMIC PATHOLOGY - HISTOLOGY))",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>PARKWAY LABORATORY SERVICES LTD.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Work collaboratively with consultant pathologists and pathology staff to ensure timely and accurate processing and staining of histology specimens for diagnostic examination. Perform shift and call-back duties to support continuous laboratory operations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Accession and charge histology specimens daily using the Laboratory Information System and Hospital System to ensure accurate specimen tracking and billing</li><li>Label and handle request forms and specimens correctly to prepare for subsequent technical processing and maintain specimen integrity</li><li>Assist consultant pathologists by trimming specimens to facilitate precise diagnostic evaluation</li><li>Apply photographic techniques to document specimens as required</li><li>Process histology blocks by labeling, embedding, tissue processing, and sectioning to produce quality samples for analysis</li><li>Perform staining, labeling, and mounting of slides using routine and special staining techniques to prepare slides for pathologist reporting</li><li>File and store specimens, slides, and blocks according to laboratory regulations to ensure proper archival and retrieval</li><li>Assist consultant pathologists in performing frozen sections in operating theatres to support intraoperative diagnosis</li><li>Supervise junior or new staff and provide on-the-job training to ensure competency and adherence to protocols</li><li>Prepare and maintain current work instruction manuals and monitor staff compliance to standard operating procedures</li><li>Manage inventory levels of laboratory supplies via the computer system and take corrective actions to prevent shortages</li><li>Review daily quality control (QC) results and collaborate with consultant pathologists to identify and address areas for improvement</li><li>Ensure compliance with regulatory guidelines and participate in hospital quality assurance programs and audits to uphold laboratory standards</li><li>Support senior medical technologists and section managers in supervision, problem-solving, quality control, safety, budgeting, purchasing, and audit activities</li><li>Act as deputy or in-charge of the Histology Department in the absence of senior staff to maintain operational continuity</li><li>Adapt to flexible staffing requirements and perform additional duties as assigned by management</li></ul>",
